{
  "texts": [
    "Another advantage is that it reduces the operations required to map the search query to the image.Following on from [38], Yoon et al.",
    "propose IRSGS (Image Retrieval with Scene Graph Similarity) [73], which makes use of a semantic graph.",
    "Given a query image, the model will generate a semantic graph and compare its similarity with graphs of images in the database.",
    "This graph comparison is achieved by taking the inner product of graph embeddings generated by a GNN (either GCN [134] or GIN [135]).",
    "One key contribution of the paper is the concept of Surrogate Relevance, which is the similarity between the captions of the images being compared."
  ]
}